Date: 16/6/1934
Source: Hawera Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 7
Edition:
Quote: This condition of affairs [pasture deterioration] has been explained by the statement that the country has become 'sheep-sick', a rather vague term which serves to cover a multitude of sins in management. To understand the cure, one must appreciate the causes of 'sheep-sick' pasture. The development of a sheep-sick condition is very rapid.
